Shared Responsibility Model

Microsoft Azure operates under a Shared Responsibility Model, where responsibilities are shared between Microsoft and the customer.

Microsoft Responsibilities

- Physical security of data centers
- Hardware maintenance
- Network infrastructure
- Cloud platform availability
- Host operating system security

Customer Responsibilities

- User account and identity management
- Access control and permissions
- Data protection and backups
- Virtual machine configuration
- Application and workload security

For this deployment, Microsoft manages the underlying cloud infrastructure while the customer manages the deployed virtual machine, user access, and resource configurations.

